            <div class="section-tag">Excel</div>
            <h2 class="art-h2">What is Excel-Based Lead Management</h2>
            <p class="art-p">Excel is commonly used by businesses to track leads, customers and sales. It provides basic tracking functionality that works well in the beginning.</p>
            <ul class="art-list">
                <li>Leads and prospects</li>
                <li>Customer contact details</li>
                <li>Follow-up dates</li>
                <li>Sales status</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="art-quote">
                <p>While Excel provides basic tracking, it lacks automation, reminders and collaboration features required for growing businesses.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
